---
description: Use UUID in URLs instead of numeric IDs — hard-to-guess detail routes
alwaysApply: true
---

# UUID URLs (No Numeric IDs in Routes)

Never expose auto-increment `id` in URLs. Use **UUID** for detail pages and API show routes.

```
✅ /berita/detail/9f3c2a1b-4e5d-6f7a-8b9c-0d1e2f3a4b5c
❌ /berita/detail/42
❌ /api/v1/news/17
```

Keep `id` as internal primary key; add `uuid` column for external references.

## Database

```php
$table->uuid('uuid')->unique();
// index if filtered often:
$table->index('uuid');
```

Generate on create:

```php
// Model boot or HasUuids trait
protected static function booted(): void
{
    static::creating(function (Model $model): void {
        $model->uuid ??= (string) Str::uuid();
    });
}
```

## Backend routes

```php
// ✅ GOOD — bind by uuid
Route::get('news/{news:uuid}', [NewsController::class, 'show']);
Route::get('pmb/track/{registration:uuid}', [PmbController::class, 'track']);

// ❌ BAD
Route::get('news/{id}', ...);
Route::apiResource('news', ...); // default {news} = numeric id
```

Override route key on model:

```php
public function getRouteKeyName(): string
{
    return 'uuid';
}
```

Repository lookup:

```php
public function findByUuid(string $uuid): ?Model
{
    return $this->remember($this->cacheKey('findByUuid', ['uuid' => $uuid]), fn () =>
        $this->newQuery()->where('uuid', $uuid)->first()
    );
}
```

## API responses

Expose `uuid` in API Resources for client routing. Omit or hide numeric `id` from public JSON when possible.

## Frontend

```tsx
// ✅ GOOD
<Route path="/berita/detail/:uuid" element={<NewsDetailPage />} />
navigate(`/berita/detail/${news.uuid}`)

// ❌ BAD
<Route path="/berita/detail/:id" element={<NewsDetailPage />} />
```

React Query keys use `uuid`: `newsKeys.detail(uuid)`.

## Slugs vs UUID

| Use case | URL key |
|----------|---------|
| Public SEO listing (optional) | `slug` in path is OK for marketing pages |
| Detail, admin, private, PMB track | **UUID only** — not numeric `id` |

Authorization still required — UUID prevents enumeration, not access control.
